css:
  .imger {
    display:       inline-block;
    width:         350px;
    text-align:    center;
  }
  .imger2 {
    width: 800px;
  }
  .mb {
    margin-bottom: 30px;
  }
  .mt {
    margin-top: 30px;
  }

table.table.table-sm
  tr
    td
      h2 Demo Time
    td[align='right']
      a[href="/bot/home"] Bot Home
  tr
    td[colspan=2 style='padding-bottom: 20px; padding-top: 20px;']
      p Two things happen after a contract is formed:<br/>
      .imger.mb
        img[src="/img/PR.png" style='height: 150px;']
        br
        u Step 1: Developer submits a pull request.
      .imger.mb
        img[src="/img/CLOSE.png" style='height: 150px;']
        br
        u Step 2: Project maintainer closes the issue.
      p Then when the maturation date is reached, the contract
        is resolved by examining issue status (open or closed).
      | For demonstration purposes, you can move the system time forward, past the maturation date.
  tr
    td[colspan=2]
      .imger
        b> Real Day
        = Time.now.strftime("%b %d")
      .imger
        b> Demo Day
        | #{BugmTime.now.strftime("%b %d")} (offset #{BugmTime.day_offset} days)
  tr
    td[colspan=2]
      .imger2
        table.table-bordered.table-condensed.table-hover.mb.mt[style='width: 100%;']
          tr
            th
            th Dec 12
            th Dec 20
            th Dec 28
            th Jan 5
          tr
            td # Closed Issues
            td = @history.period(0)["closed_issues"]
            td = @history.period(1)["closed_issues"]
            td = @history.period(2)["closed_issues"]
            td = @history.period(3)["closed_issues"]
          tr
            td # Resolved Contracts
            td = @history.period(0)["resolved_contracts"]
            td = @history.period(1)["resolved_contracts"]
            td = @history.period(2)["resolved_contracts"]
            td = @history.period(3)["resolved_contracts"]
          tr
            td Account Balance
            td = @history.period(0)["balance"]
            td = @history.period(1)["balance"]
            td = @history.period(2)["balance"]
            td = @history.period(3)["balance"]

  tr
    td: b Increment System Day Offset
    td
      a[href="/bot/timeinc"] Move the system forward eight days, close three issues, resolve matured contracts
      p
      | <span style='color: red;'>WARNING</span>: the system time can only be moved forward, not back!<br/>
        To reset the system days offset to zero, you must rebuild the system
        from scratch.

